data.name: btn_test_system_speaker.ToolTip
data.value: This button plays a short tune through the system speaker to test the system speaker on your computer.

data.name: label_test_system_speaker_message.Text
data.value: If you do not hear any sound, you can use the "Use sound card to create beep" feature.

data.name: comboBox_theme.ToolTip
data.value: Change the theme of the program

data.name: label_test_system_speaker_message_2.Text
data.value: Testing the system speaker is not available on computers that do not have a system speaker output, or on computers with a non-standard system speaker output.

data.name: label_test_system_speaker_message_3.Text
data.value: On compact computers and computers of unknown type, you may not hear any sound or may cause instability or undesirable behavior when the system speaker is tested because the main speakers may be connected to the system speaker output instead of the actual system speaker.

data.name: label_create_beep_from_soundcard_automatically_activated_message_2.Text
data.value: The "Use sound card to create beep" feature is automatically enabled because the computer is a compact computer or its type is unknown.

data.name: label_create_beep_from_soundcard_automatically_activated_message_1.Text
data.value: The "Use sound card to create beep" feature is permanently enabled because the system speaker output is not detected, or the system speaker output is non-standard.

data.name: button_show_reason.Text
data.value: Show the reason for this situation

data.name: checkBox1.Text
data.value: Never automatically being silent while a music is playing

data.name: checkBox_enable_create_beep_from_soundcard.Text
data.value: Use sound card to create beep

data.name: checkBox_enable_create_beep_from_soundcard.ToolTip
data.value: Use sound card instead of system speaker to create beep

data.name: checkBox_use_motor_speed_mod.Text
data.value: Use Motor-speed mod or buzzer (via Arduino, Raspberry Pi or ESP32)
